Title: Object: An Egyptian Mirror
Description: Egyptian sculpted mirror handle; a bare lady on the handle, with a headdress; surmounted by two large horns facing down. 1909 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Sir David Young Cameron
Curator's comments: According to Rinder this mirrow could belong to Dynasty XVIII. See 1910-1-24-3 for related print.
Bibliographic references: Rinder 1912 / D.Y. Cameron: An illustrated catalogue of his etched work with introductory essay and descriptive notes on each plate (408.II)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir David Young Cameron
